The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Burdwan, Aug. 30: A mob in Burdwans Memari set a ration dealers house on fire today, accusing him of selling the items in the black market.    
	The villagers then ransacked the local gram panchayat office. They also locked up a team of food inspectors who had come to Swapan Mondals shop to probe the charge of irregularities. When police cane-charged the protesters, they threw stones at the cops. Mondal is absconding.        
	Burdwan: A man was allegedly beaten to death by a youth in Katwa for refusing to marry his daughter to him. Uddhav Debnath, 24, has been arrested        
	Tamluk: A court has refused to return the truck driven by Gurjant Singh to its owner Narinder Singh as the forensic report on the vehicle is yet to be received.
                                                                                                                                                      
